<p>NOTE- Kodak 1996 net earnings total $1.288 billion or $3.82 per share, versus $1.252 billion, or $3.67 per share for 1995; for the fourth quarter, net earnings were $164 million, or $.49 per share, compared with $275 million or $.80 per share for the 1995 fourth quarter.  However, excluding restructuring costs, the loss on the Office Imaging sale and earnings from discontinued operations, full year earnings were $1.519 billion or $4.50 per share.  On the same basis, earnings for the fourth quarter were $395 million or $1.19 per share.</p>
<p>The company's results for the fourth quarter and year included: -  After-tax restructuring costs of $256 million. - An after-tax loss of $252 million related to the sale of the Office Imaging business. -  After-tax income of $277 million from discontinued operations associated with the sale of the non-imaging health businesses in 1994.</p>
